Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.04,0:00:04.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even when encountering a huge wall, with friends it will soon become a large door.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.38,0:00:09.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Today is a one hour special. A long awaited travelling play. A showdown at the Konpira theatre.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.92,0:00:14.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seeing the one truth, while looking like a child, having the brains of an adult. His name is Detective Conan.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.47,0:02:04.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, father. After we finally came to Shikoku.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.87,0:02:03.74,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Shikoku = Smallest of the four main islands of Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.74,0:02:06.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's better to eat rather than to drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.50,0:02:09.87,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,"Sanuki" is the region name of Kagawa prefecture where udon noodles were first brought from China to Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.50,0:02:07.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sanuki Udon!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.79,0:02:13.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay, okay... But before that, let me wet my lips a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.38,0:02:14.80,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Udon = Thick wheat noodles, usually served in a hot broth.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.55,0:02:17.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you do that, I won't be responsible if you fall asleep during the play.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.38,0:02:20.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right. After we finally get to meet Tamanousuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.72,0:02:23.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I get it already...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.47,0:02:29.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, the Kanemaruza theatre where Tamandusuke and others are doing the play is really famous, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.81,0:02:28.56,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Kanemaruza = The oldest kabuki theatre still in use in Japan, was built at Konpira in the early 19th century.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.02,0:02:33.98,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Kabuki = Japanese classical drama.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.02,0:02:34.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right. Every spring they perform the Konpira kabuki play...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.23,0:02:38.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...and people around the nation come to see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.28,0:02:42.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, look, look!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.66,0:02:43.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right. Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.33,0:02:46.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm looking forward to this!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.29,0:02:53.92,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The phantom of the theatre
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.87,0:02:53.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The phantom of the theatre.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.92,0:02:59.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is an udon restaurant?! It's just someone's home.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.59,0:03:01.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Welcome!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.84,0:03:07.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ohhh! Well, well! There seem to be snacks to go with the beer.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.27,0:03:08.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They are toppings for udon, father.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.91,0:03:11.44,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Piping hot:\N{\b1}Hot{\b0} udon and {\b1}hot{\b0} fish soup\NHot and cold:\N{\b1}Hot{\b0} udon and {\b1}cold{\b0} fish soup\NCold and hot:\N{\b1}Cold{\b0} udon and {\b1}hot{\b0} fish soup\NLukewarm:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.85,0:03:11.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you for waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.85,0:03:12.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, here they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.48,0:03:14.86,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Tempura = Deep-fried fish and vegetables in a light batter.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.48,0:03:15.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tempura is over there, you may choose how much you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.24,0:03:22.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.12,0:03:27.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They just take your tongue with them! This is really the real taste.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.91,0:03:32.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This has really opened my eyes! It's come to this, so I'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.92,0:03:35.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I mean that. That.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.13,0:03:40.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Sanuki Udon roaming eating contest?"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.21,0:03:40.76,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Sanuki-Udon\Neating contest by trying the food at various restaurants
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.68,0:03:43.26,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Start of the Temple road
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.68,0:03:45.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You two young ladies. Here, use these canes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.05,0:03:47.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Return them on your way down, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.31,0:03:48.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.06,0:03:50.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.98,0:03:54.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A cane? I'm not that old...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.28,0:04:02.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly, how many are there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.15,0:04:08.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see... To the Main Sanctuary there are 785 steps in total.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.04,0:04:10.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seven hundred...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.33,0:04:11.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And eighty-five.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.54,0:04:14.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.96,0:04:18.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I should have used this from the beginning. Since there is something this useful!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.71,0:04:21.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Where is father?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.01,0:04:22.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.01,0:04:25.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.59,0:04:27.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As expected, local sake is on a different level.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.60,0:04:29.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.56,0:04:32.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about the shrine visit?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.89,0:04:34.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry. Pray for me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.15,0:04:40.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, Kanemaruza is right over there. I'll wait here. Obachan, one more!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.40,0:04:43.15,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Obachan = Cuter version of obasan (an endearing term for an unrelated older woman)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.99,0:04:44.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happened to tasting udon at different restaurants?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.17,0:05:01.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm finally here. Carrying me only half-way is unfair.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.92,0:05:03.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're slow, Sonoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.88,0:05:06.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You could've stayed down and rest with my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.09,0:05:09.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute! Don't compare me with him!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.97,0:05:12.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Konpira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} is a Sea's Guardian Deity, right-?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.68,0:05:17.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true. The people who work at sea receive courteous blessings; this says...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.56,0:05:21.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's almost time. Shall we go to the Kanemaruza?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.23,0:05:25.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've been waiting for this! I wonder if Tamanousuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} is doing good?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.49,0:05:27.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Renge{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.86,0:05:29.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right. That's the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.70,0:05:33.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are they like "love-love" yet, those two?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.91,0:05:36.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Target or not... Ah, Tamanousuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.21,0:05:37.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Sonoko...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.25,0:05:40.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haha... Every single person...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.46,0:05:45.09,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Originally aired on: September 11th, 2006\NStory based on manga: TV Original
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.51,0:05:47.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Welcome, all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.05,0:05:50.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You had a long way to walk. We can't thank you enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.51,0:05:52.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is hopeless.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.06,0:05:53.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those two.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.81,0:05:56.31,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Kataoka Renge (17)\NActress
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.81,0:05:56.31,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Itou Tamanosuke (17)\NChairman
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.35,0:05:56.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just look at them, all love-love.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.39,0:05:58.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.06,0:06:00.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Megumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.94,0:06:01.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.23,0:06:03.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.86,0:06:06.49,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Itou Megumi (7)\NChild actor and Tamanosuke's little sister
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.44,0:06:06.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are no little kids today.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.86,0:06:07.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, you mean them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.57,0:06:10.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They had some things to do, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.70,0:06:12.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's good. Megumi is so happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.16,0:06:14.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hey, Megumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.24,0:06:17.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This, this... Isn't the kid with glasses popular?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.87,0:06:20.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.08,0:06:22.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here you go?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.55,0:06:25.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The entry way is low, so be careful with your head.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.01,0:06:29.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this about a low entrance...?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.68,0:06:31.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Father!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.01,0:06:33.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you alright?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.06,0:06:35.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought he would do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.48,0:06:41.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We are still in the middle of preparations and a bit busy, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.11,0:06:44.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Woah, how wonderful!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.65,0:06:49.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, right now, at the stage, they are checking if the Seri is working.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.13,0:06:52.45,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Seri
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.99,0:06:50.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seri?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.24,0:06:54.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Several people push it up from the basement.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.45,0:06:56.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The actor comes out from there and takes a pose.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.50,0:07:04.34,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Rotating Stage
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.50,0:06:58.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The stage is moving!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.29,0:07:04.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's a Rotating-Stage. Again, there are many people in the basement rotating it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.59,0:07:05.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Using the same method as in the olden days.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.38,0:07:08.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About the basement, it's called "Naraku".
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.26,0:07:14.22,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Naraku = Theatre basement, also means Hell
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.26,0:07:14.22,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Naraku
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.26,0:07:13.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the olden days the drainage was bad, so the people in the basement had a hard time, hence that name.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.06,0:07:17.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This road is called Hanamichi, the audience to stage passage!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.04,0:07:22.15,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Hanamichi
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.22,0:07:21.60,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Hanamichi = The passage through audience to stage
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.22,0:07:21.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After a signal, the actor-goes through the audience to the stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.52,0:07:28.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the way, there is "Suppon". Just like Seri, it's lifted from below.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.49,0:07:33.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then, right above the Hanamichi, there is a crane like "Kakesuji".
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.15,0:07:33.99,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Kakesuji
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.45,0:07:36.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Once connected, the actor can fly all over the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.12,0:07:38.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Amazing...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.00,0:07:44.33,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Sakura = Cherry blossom
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.00,0:07:44.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The ceiling is patterned with bamboo and from up there they make Sakura snow storms, like they used to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.27,0:07:44.79,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Grape rack
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.79,0:07:48.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uwaa! It's like a time trip to 100 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.38,0:07:49.67,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Balcony seats
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.32,0:07:49.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.80,0:07:51.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Far from 100 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.18,0:07:57.26,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The Edo (or Tokugawa), period ran from 1603 to 1867.\NThe Tenpou period was from around 1830 to 1843.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.18,0:07:57.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Firstly, this Kanemaruza was built as a Shogun forte and office at the end of the Edo era at the Tenpou period.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.56,0:08:01.35,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Shogun = Supreme general of the samurai, equivalent to a "general": A high officer in an army.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.56,0:08:01.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Becoming a partial payment of a debt, it became the best Japanese theatre there is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.19,0:08:05.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To be able to do a play here... It really makes me feel like an actress.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.02,0:08:08.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Plus, you two are all love-love...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.19,0:08:16.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sonoko! Ah, I heard that you are performing the Phantom of the Opera today, but in a different era.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.62,0:08:24.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right. A showy play in stage, an ugly face poorly hidden, a mysterious phantom and a sweet songstress.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.13,0:08:29.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And their love story develops to love and hatred, a fearful play.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.26,0:08:33.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But instead of Opera... The Phantom of the Konpira!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.98,0:08:56.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Beloved daughter, sing! For your loved one, me, the angel of song, sing! Sing, I say!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.12,0:09:02.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, noble angel! Shining angel! Carry my soul to the heavens!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.79,0:09:04.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You cannot sing!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.21,0:09:08.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Open your eyes! That is a devil! A revengeful ghost!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.38,0:09:12.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fantastic...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.59,0:09:14.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey. Who is that person?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.63,0:09:18.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one who is supporting the play this time, Rausu Tatsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.60,0:09:19.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A sponsor, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.18,0:09:21.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Rausu..."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.60,0:09:23.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From Rausu Companies, Kansai, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.93,0:09:25.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think I read about it in a newspaper...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.73,0:09:29.98,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Rausu Tatsuhiko (27)\NSponsor
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.73,0:09:31.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His father passed away and the young son was just recently appointed as the successor, or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.11,0:09:38.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, way. Oh, no. Why so suddenly...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.91,0:09:42.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Pleased to meet you, I'm Suzuki Sonoko!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.37,0:09:44.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do your best, Renge.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.50,0:09:45.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes! Renge!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.83,0:09:50.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because this Rausu Tatsuhiko is with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.09,0:09:55.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you. But I have a small role in this play, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.72,0:10:01.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About that... The heroine songstress is Renge. If we negotiate about a change...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.22,0:10:02.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rausu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.76,0:10:05.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's decided by the chairman, me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.27,0:10:07.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not you, the sponsor.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.94,0:10:09.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not to mention, I'm not the phantom either.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.36,0:10:11.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.77,0:10:12.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Phantom?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.94,0:10:14.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not because the request isn't firm enough, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.53,0:10:16.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Obviously not!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.61,0:10:20.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I only wanted to see my child-hood friend's hour of triumph.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.49,0:10:30.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Request. A change of heroine. A child-hood friend and a phantom. This is almost like...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.71,0:10:37.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Phantom of the Opera. Opera-za no kaijin, there's no way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.26,0:10:42.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A child-hood friend of Renge{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, huh... But isn't this...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.93,0:10:45.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't it be better if you would be a little more honest, Tamanousuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.79,0:10:46.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.98,0:10:50.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why don't you confess your feelings to Renge? You like her, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.40,0:10:51.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,R-Rausu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.52,0:10:55.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you stay hesitating, I'll steal her.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.07,0:11:00.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Love triangle!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.41,0:11:01.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sonoko!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.45,0:11:04.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't really mind, chairman.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.37,0:11:07.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Changing roles with Renge{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.62,0:11:10.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you saying? Stop joking.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.58,0:11:15.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you understand why you are in this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.42,0:11:21.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right. And as a long time fan of Romi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}... Just sharing the stage with you will make me happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.51,0:11:23.51,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Karube Romi (22)\NActress
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.84,0:11:23.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.97,0:11:27.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow, what a beauty! I feel like I've seen her somewhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.18,0:11:31.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Karube Romi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. A famous young actress.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.19,0:11:33.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She gladly accepted the heroines' role...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.15,0:11:39.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...my-brother said. He was sure that she would refuse, but she quickly said okay. That surprised him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.40,0:11:43.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, well. Excuse me for my rudeness... Please, do your best.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.74,0:11:49.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My, my. Seems that I'm hated.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.46,0:11:55.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oops. It's so dark in here, I can't see well.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.17,0:11:58.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone! Collect the performance piece by the sponsor{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.17,0:11:59.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Performance piece?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.43,0:12:03.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A filthy tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.18,0:12:07.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's luminous tape. Look! It's put on there as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.52,0:12:10.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're an intelligent boy, aren't you? That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.81,0:12:15.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the theatrical blackout, it's put here so that the actors don't get their positions wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.61,0:12:23.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Neither of them seems to be within your reach, Sonoko.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.95,0:12:27.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's totally fine. I found a different target.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.28,0:12:27.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A different target?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.91,0:12:33.08,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Kawatake Otoya (25)\NActor
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.87,0:12:35.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Finally some rehearsal, huh? It's a stage of friendship. Well, I have no interest except for my own play.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.79,0:12:37.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Somehow he's so cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.88,0:12:39.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Move, move! You're in the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.63,0:12:40.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah! We're sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.55,0:12:44.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who let these in? It's not time for guests yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.59,0:12:46.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I get the creeps from him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.89,0:12:47.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sonoko...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.14,0:12:50.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I'm sorry, Nabe{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. I forgot to introduce them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.60,0:12:53.81,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Nabeshima Katsuo (40)\NChief of stage setting
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.31,0:12:53.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here is the detective Mouri Kogoro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.39,0:12:54.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.81,0:12:56.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri Kogoro?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.02,0:12:58.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That famous...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.32,0:13:02.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I'm that famous Mouri Kogoro.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.36,0:13:05.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then, the daughter, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.61,0:13:06.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.87,0:13:07.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.74,0:13:10.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My dear Edogawa Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.79,0:13:11.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hello...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.87,0:13:12.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.75,0:13:16.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm Suzuki Sonoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}! Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.67,0:13:24.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whoever you are, I don't want you to get in the way. The predecessor was stricter.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.22,0:13:26.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad is dad. I'm me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.51,0:13:31.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, if I didn't have this job, I'd be neck deep in debts.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.85,0:13:35.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I should be thankful as well, for the chairman. Ok! Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.90,0:13:37.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't get in the way now!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.23,0:13:43.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's start.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.74,0:13:47.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Renge{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, could you bring my mouth wash from the back?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.32,0:13:48.57,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The requested mouth wash is to keep her throat clear, not to freshen up her breath.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.55,0:13:48.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.57,0:13:49.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan and the rest, go to the seats.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.16,0:13:51.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeees!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.60,0:14:14.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Romi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! Are you alright? Romi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.56,0:14:18.81,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Originally aired on: September 11th, 2006\NStory based on manga: TV Original
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.19,0:14:20.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Romi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.82,0:14:22.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.02,0:14:25.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone... an ambulance... Call an ambulance!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.86,0:14:27.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop that, chairman.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.11,0:14:30.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're exaggerating. It wasn't anything serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.99,0:14:31.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Romi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.20,0:14:39.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just a scratch. But this is quite close to the audience. It won't be good publicity if this gets out.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.00,0:14:41.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shit. Messing with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.67,0:14:44.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who did this? Clear up and fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.88,0:14:49.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I don't fix this soon, it won't make it to the show.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.05,0:14:52.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's the worst. He's got to be the criminal.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.05,0:14:53.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sonoko...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.14,0:14:55.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But first, treatment...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.52,0:14:57.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's go to backstage first, Romi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.85,0:15:01.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That rope, it seems like it's been severed with a sharp object.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.11,0:15:06.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The phantom's doings?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.07,0:15:07.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's rubbish.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.49,0:15:10.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was just someone's prank.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.49,0:15:11.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then what is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.74,0:15:15.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it had worked, we actually might've had to change the heroine.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.83,0:15:19.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That won't happen. Somehow I want to fight this now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.29,0:15:24.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The phantoms or something are trying to make us wet our pants? I won't take it. Right, chairman?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.75,0:15:28.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me... You're in the middle of something, but... A phantom?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.05,0:15:30.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the phantom of the Konpira theatre!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.97,0:15:31.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As I said, that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.43,0:15:34.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I remember correctly, it's the title of this play, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.26,0:15:36.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The phantom of the Konpira.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.93,0:15:38.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes... That's why...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.73,0:15:41.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see. It's the chandelier. Chandelier.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.48,0:15:42.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That would be it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.23,0:15:44.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Chandelier?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.40,0:15:48.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the play that will come to this stage as well, the Phantom of the Opera...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.82,0:15:54.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A chandelier falls right on the first heroine.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.70,0:16:03.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not all. It's very similar to your situation! The setup of the people in the Phantom of the Opera.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.83,0:16:08.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That reminds me, just now Tamanousuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said that the phantom's request isn't enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.46,0:16:14.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the same as well. In the Phantom of the Opera, the phantom requests the change of the heroine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.14,0:16:21.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What could this mean? It seems like everyone is hiding something big from us...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.19,0:16:24.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no. What to expect from a famous detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.86,0:16:30.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tamanousuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}. I think it would be better to discuss this matter with Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.86,0:16:33.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.66,0:16:38.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, we thought they were just pranks, by someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.87,0:16:51.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doing really nothing, only showing up to scare people, that was...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.26,0:16:55.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To deliver these letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.80,0:17:01.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmm... They are all... very alike.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.93,0:17:03.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What exactly does this mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.35,0:17:10.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Wide participation, I have interest! To be stabbed and die a glorious death! Sanuki Konpira's Phantom".
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.36,0:17:11.61,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Sanuki = An area in northern Shikoku.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.82,0:17:14.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Wide participation, I have interest." It's obviously about the play, isn't it...?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.03,0:17:18.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To say, "To be stabbed and die a glorious death" does sound very play like...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.91,0:17:21.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't it a code? About the "Sanuki" word.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.45,0:17:23.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nicely figured out, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.71,0:17:24.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sanuki?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.21,0:17:27.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This was so easy, it on the contrary bothers me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.34,0:17:38.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sanuki... Ah! I see! Reading Sanuki without-SA.\NRemoving SA syllables and then read it, right? Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.89,0:17:43.52,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Hiragana = One of the Japanese syllabaries.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.89,0:17:41.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Change them all temporarily in hiragana, and it's easy to figure out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.52,0:17:45.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And... take out the SA syllables, right? Doing that...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.60,0:17:47.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.60,0:17:49.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Change the heroine! To Renge!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.69,0:17:53.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-This is... Clearly a threatening letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.03,0:17:56.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if we would always listen to each one, we couldn't make a play!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.32,0:18:01.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly. But, if we ignore it, what happened just now...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.45,0:18:04.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Meaning, it wasn't a simple mistake, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.21,0:18:08.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means, I don't think this is over yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.50,0:18:12.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Chairman. I'm doing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.05,0:18:14.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it's okay with Romi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.51,0:18:17.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, you might just be a real actress.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.22,0:18:19.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.93,0:18:21.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it really okay, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.22,0:18:27.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Considering the situation and the threatening letter, it doesn't seem to be personal...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.94,0:18:33.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if the rope's cut, we don't know if it was really on purpose until we check into it more closely.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.86,0:18:37.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's right. At this stage, if the police would make a move...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.20,0:18:42.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Regarding to the play, we have to leave the decision to the chairman, Tamanousuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.12,0:18:47.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, it's decided. We go with these roles.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.75,0:18:50.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Today's premiere... I feel the same way for tomorrow's show.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.21,0:18:52.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I want you all to do your best.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.31,0:19:10.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Earnestly, beloved daughter!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.78,0:19:19.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Believe in me and sing! Who believes in me, shall not die!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.45,0:19:21.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.66,0:19:27.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please wait! Are you a god? Or else... a devil?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.45,0:19:33.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That is a devil. Here is your punishment! The dweller of the world without light... of the world of darkness!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.55,0:19:39.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You foolish and rude youngster. Being cursed, you shall be!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.22,0:19:46.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My love, my spirit, if you desire to bind them, you shall become revengeful to the world of darkness!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.81,0:19:47.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm so touched...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.23,0:19:54.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I knew it... It's because father drank so much again.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.52,0:19:58.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For a while now, what is that woman looking at?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.69,0:19:59.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.82,0:20:05.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hm? What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.95,0:20:08.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.67,0:20:15.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who is it, screwing around?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.34,0:20:19.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.38,0:20:22.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's the matter? That voice...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.18,0:20:25.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's almost like...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.55,0:20:26.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A frog?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.39,0:20:30.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.77,0:20:33.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This too is alike, with the Phantom of the Opera.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.90,0:20:34.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.16,0:20:48.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shit... Where did it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.66,0:20:51.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The curtain. Close the curtain. Romi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, come back here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.63,0:20:58.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.97,0:21:10.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the only path, but... None of the guests seem to have seen a phantom going through here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.56,0:21:12.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why, exactly...?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.19,0:21:22.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, brat! What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.15,0:21:26.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ehh, umm... It was so high, it seemed interesting...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.95,0:21:29.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This isn't an amusement park! Only staff personal are allowed here!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.78,0:21:31.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.14,0:21:34.66,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Karube Romi
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.79,0:21:34.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone changed Romi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s mouth wash?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.42,0:21:43.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She thought it was the same wash, then the curtain opened, and she went to the stage like that. And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.76,0:21:45.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's mean. Who would do such a thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.63,0:21:47.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You, you can't think...!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.22,0:21:52.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That doesn't matter. Right now I have to think what to do with this play.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.60,0:21:55.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You rehearsed with Romi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.85,0:21:58.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The lines, you should know them, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.44,0:22:00.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-You don't mean I...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.57,0:22:03.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no time to grumble about trivial things. The customers are waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.70,0:22:10.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The curtain is down. In fifteen minutes, I'm raising the curtain.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.66,0:22:15.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.29,0:22:22.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A phantom? Obviously just someone spiteful...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.88,0:22:25.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The other customers seem to think so too.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.47,0:22:28.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where is Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.35,0:22:34.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A dead end, huh? This is almost like a maze.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.44,0:22:44.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anxious, loved daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.49,0:22:50.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is not too good... Where am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.62,0:22:57.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...if I can. Be Romi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s substitute actor.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.87,0:22:59.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.83,0:23:03.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I am... in luck with the angel of song.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.60,0:23:17.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No one is here. What was that...?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.81,0:23:18.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No one is here. What was that...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.85,0:23:24.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To have met that person, my heart has been filled with joy!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.82,0:23:29.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that person is a dweller of darkness. I wish to be taken by that darkness...!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.70,0:23:35.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop this talk about the world of darkness. I shall guide you to the world where there's light!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.41,0:23:38.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wherever, as your friend...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.16,0:23:40.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}! Where did you go?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.21,0:23:40.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To the toilet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.17,0:23:44.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please, swear. You will only love me!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.42,0:23:47.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I shall swear. I will only love you!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.51,0:23:52.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You cannot go back anymore!\NYou shall die on this road!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.01,0:23:56.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everything will end, everything will vanish in the darkness! Like this oath!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.93,0:24:03.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I shall not fear your true appearance. What I fear is that warped heart of yours!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.27,0:24:05.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Amazing, Renge{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.77,0:24:07.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You wouldn't think she was a substitute.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.82,0:24:09.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huge success, Renge{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.69,0:24:12.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That substitute's acting was magnificent, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.91,0:24:15.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm looking forward to tomorrow's play.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.93,0:24:33.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This place gives me the creeps...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.91,0:24:56.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is...! What on earth...?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.29,0:25:00.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nabe{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.79,0:25:03.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't move! Don't move from there.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.00,0:25:07.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,N-No! You're wrong! It wasn't me! It wasn't me!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.22,0:25:19.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did you say? Tamanosuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was apprehended by the police?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.85,0:25:20.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.60,0:25:23.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Save... Conan... My brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.77,0:25:24.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Calm down, Megumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.19,0:25:26.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why on earth was he taken in for?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.02,0:25:30.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That is... The stage setter, Nabeshima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}... They say he killed him!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.99,0:25:37.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way Tamanosuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} would do something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.24,0:25:42.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, they said that he was found unconscious next to Nabeshima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, holding a knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.50,0:25:43.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean he had fainted?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.04,0:25:48.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And he was also wearing the phantom's mask, which was covered in blood...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.42,0:25:53.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So they are saying that every phantom incident until now was the chairman's doing!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.67,0:25:56.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no... Father. Let's go to the police immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.55,0:25:57.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.06,0:26:05.06,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Interrogation Room 1
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.06,0:26:05.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were asked to come with a letter?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.48,0:26:09.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Be gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.11,0:26:17.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I want to put flowers to the small dying village. Stone monument's morning, at the base I will wait. Rausu"
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.66,0:26:20.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could this also be a part of the Sanuki code?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.78,0:26:24.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's alike with that threatening letter from that phantom of the Konpira theatre.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.83,0:26:25.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.12,0:26:29.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you put it in normal hiragana...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.63,0:26:36.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I want to talk about Renge. I will wait near the stone monument,"
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.84,0:26:38.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, when you went to the crime scene...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.23,0:26:50.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.11,0:26:53.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, why would someone do something like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.90,0:26:57.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because he's the phantom of the Konpira.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.78,0:27:04.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To get the heroine changed, sending threatening letters, dropping the paper lanterns on Romi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.79,0:27:08.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...and changing her mouth wash... That's the only thing you can think of!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.21,0:27:15.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About that... Rausu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is saying the exact same thing. That you called him there.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.92,0:27:23.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no! I'm not saying that Tamanosuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} is the phantom! Just... that he did call me there.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.43,0:27:25.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With this, night?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.81,0:27:35.27,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Be gone! I want to put flowers to the small dying village\NPublic park's morning, at the base I will wait\NTamanosuke
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.81,0:27:29.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A same kind of letter with the exact same content was delivered to Tamanosuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, he says.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.02,0:27:35.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Only difference is, is that the park was a stone monument. And the sender, was you.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.57,0:27:37.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And so, did you go?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.36,0:27:40.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I went, alright. But Tamanosuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} didn't come.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.78,0:27:44.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Obviously. Because at that time he was at the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.49,0:27:49.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, did you meet or see anyone at the park?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.66,0:27:51.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's the ease...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.96,0:27:57.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Romi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.97,0:28:04.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, you didn't notice Rausu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, but you were at the park, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.51,0:28:05.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What were you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.39,0:28:12.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.21,0:28:16.21,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Criminal affairs section\NKonpira murder affair and searching investigations.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.65,0:28:17.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-This is an honour, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! To be able to investigate with you...!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.03,0:28:25.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You have evidence to suspect Itou Tamanosuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, because he was holding a knife in his hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.79,0:28:29.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Tamanosuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was unconscious, wasn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.50,0:28:33.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's possible that someone else made him hold it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.04,0:28:34.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.00,0:28:35.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it, that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.29,0:28:37.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, regarding about that...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.46,0:28:40.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Indeed there was a bump at the back of his head...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.22,0:28:47.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he could've also fought with the victim, slipped and hit his head to the different level.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.31,0:28:49.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Different level?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.35,0:28:52.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.94,0:29:00.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, yes. Right behind the fallen victim was a big memorial stone. The pedestal was the different level.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.15,0:29:03.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the motive for the crime...?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.70,0:29:05.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's obviously money.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.37,0:29:12.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They were staff for the previous chairman, and he wanted the chairman pay off his loan...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.29,0:29:15.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...and the victim was pushing it a bit too much. And then, finally...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.71,0:29:16.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.79,0:29:17.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's a lie, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.84,0:29:20.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One more thing. This is important.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.34,0:29:28.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Framing Rausu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} as the phantom of the Konpira and thus getting Renge{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s feelings toward himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.85,0:29:32.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's exactly weird. Because, from the beginning, those two were...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.48,0:29:37.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All love-love. Even though it's mortifying. He has no need to do such a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.73,0:29:41.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As I'm saying... Isn't that exactly the reason Rausu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} appeared?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.86,0:29:46.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't tell from a woman and a man by just looking the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.37,0:29:51.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The manuscript is impossible now.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.83,0:29:53.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The chairman is a suspect...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.75,0:29:54.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's such a shame.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.83,0:29:57.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She .wasn't,half-bad, Kataoka Renge.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.55,0:30:04.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You believe in Tamanousuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.26,0:30:09.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The chairman believed in me too. That's why I was Romi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s substitute.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.97,0:30:11.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.18,0:30:15.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, I was scared. I thought I definitely couldn't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.35,0:30:21.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, the angel of song... the phantom encouraged me!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.40,0:30:22.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.65,0:30:24.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It isn't you, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.90,0:30:26.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you doubting me?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.74,0:30:30.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know! What or who should I believe? I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.62,0:30:34.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you are in this much anguish, you should just quit this play!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.71,0:30:38.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Renge. I want you to live with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.00,0:30:41.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.09,0:30:47.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I apologize. I am now only worried about chairman and only that...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.22,0:30:50.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that so? I understand. Then tell this to that chairman.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.60,0:30:56.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As a sponsor, the damage, is too great. It's regrettable, but as it is, I have to withdraw my hands from this.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.64,0:30:57.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.94,0:31:01.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, you are another stony. I will definitely not give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.19,0:31:09.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry. We had no intention to eavesdrop, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.95,0:31:13.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, is it really true? That the phantom encouraged you?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.16,0:31:19.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I can't be honestly happy. Because of the encouragement, I did well with the play.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.75,0:31:21.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not true. It's your true talent.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.25,0:31:29.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But changing the heroine to the new one, it's the same again, isn't it? With the Phantom of the Opera.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.34,0:31:31.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right. I'm afraid of that too.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.72,0:31:33.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who exactly is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.85,0:31:37.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it's not Tamanosuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} Then of course, Rausu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.31,0:31:41.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or rather a real phantom? A ghost? A monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.98,0:31:43.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No. That can't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.41,0:31:53.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is it!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.20,0:31:57.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.16,0:31:59.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.21,0:32:04.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right. A wireless one. Probably with this...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.17,0:32:09.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To tell you the truth, I heard the phantom as well that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.43,0:32:13.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means... In other words...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.89,0:32:17.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It means that the phantom of the Konpira is not a ghost or a monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.35,0:32:20.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm going to ask my father again.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.35,0:32:21.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll come too.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.52,0:32:23.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have to hurry too.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.69,0:32:29.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are things that were bothering me from the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.53,0:32:37.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The threatening Sanuki letters. Imitating the Phantom of the Opera to the phantom of the Konpira's behaviour.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.29,0:32:42.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it either wanted to be found or someone witnessing it, I can understand the reasoning.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.63,0:32:47.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But a murder is going one step too far. Maybe there's a hint there...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.76,0:32:56.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A difference in level, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.89,0:32:59.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the ideal place for the criminal to hide...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.33,0:33:19.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Father! Can't you do something?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.45,0:33:24.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After coming all this way... At this rate, Tamanosuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}'s stage will be forever gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.96,0:33:26.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You don't have to worry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.38,0:33:32.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just now I got a call from Oonishi officer. Itou Tamanosuke was released as innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.43,0:33:38.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In exchange, Rausu Tatsuhiko was apprehended with circumstantial evidence, it seems.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.85,0:33:40.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This time there is no mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.31,0:33:44.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the cane that is used to climb the stone steps to the crime scene...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.60,0:33:48.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...they found not only the victim's fingerprints, but Rausu Tatsuhiko's as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.36,0:33:55.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We think that they fought and his fingerprints got on the cane. Moreover, from his car...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.87,0:34:06.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't joke around! I don't know about any cane! And I don't remember putting those things in my car!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.08,0:34:11.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At yesterday's premiere a certain phantom made an appearance and caused a huge uproar.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.17,0:34:15.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Most of the guests thought it was part of the play, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.63,0:34:18.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Projector! Didn't you use that at that time, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.69,0:34:30.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see... It was done like that! D-Don't joke! I wouldn't do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.15,0:34:36.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you use a remote control, even from your seat you can control the projector, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.99,0:34:37.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.03,0:34:43.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then, a tape-recorder and a transmitter. By hiding these, you did the phantoms voice to Renge{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.33,0:34:48.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To get her moved. We even found the speaker near the ceiling.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.42,0:34:56.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was all to get her feelings to yourself! That's why you framed Tamanosuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. That's the way it is, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.38,0:34:57.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't joke!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.47,0:35:02.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Brother! Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.80,0:35:02.10,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Onii{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}! = Honourable big brother, with a cute suffix.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.89,0:35:04.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I made you worry. And the others?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.48,0:35:06.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.73,0:35:10.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's go. In any case, we have to think what to do with the show.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.27,0:35:12.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.44,0:35:16.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The problem is, after all, that pedestal.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.45,0:35:20.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the criminal attacked Nabeshima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} from up there...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.24,0:35:25.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Originally aired on: September 11th, 2006\NStory based on manga: TV Original
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.25,0:35:30.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right! Alibi... I have an alibi!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.29,0:35:33.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Too bad, but that also...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.92,0:35:37.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The speak practice in that park was a lie?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.76,0:35:40.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She had been scared of being dropped from the role.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.39,0:35:46.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"If I would be an important witness for the sponsor, Rausu..." she thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.85,0:35:48.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what she's saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.81,0:35:52.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? Why would she do such a thing...?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.57,0:35:54.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hm? What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.15,0:35:57.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me. Could I go to the restroom?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.86,0:36:01.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One more thing. The projector that played the phantom.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.95,0:36:05.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Controlling it with a remote controller... That's possible from somewhere else too.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.95,0:36:08.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right. Like above the stage!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.75,0:36:10.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, officer.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.46,0:36:12.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, you are Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.08,0:36:16.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} told me to ask you something...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.55,0:36:18.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} did? What?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.67,0:36:21.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where were Rausu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s fingerprints on the cane?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.01,0:36:23.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, that. They were on the tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.22,0:36:29.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right. A different coloured and shining like daylight. Well, it was a mark after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.31,0:36:31.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From which store did it come?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.02,0:36:35.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About that... There hasn't been a store to claim it as theirs...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.02,0:36:40.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because it was performance tape, I thought we would find it immediately, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.61,0:36:42.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Performance tape!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.91,0:36:49.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see... I figured it out. I figured out the real culprit!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.91,0:36:52.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rausu Tatsuhiko has escaped!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.58,0:36:57.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm deeply sorry. When I looked away for a little moment...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.34,0:36:58.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Call an alarm! Hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.23,0:37:13.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You do not love me! Don't love me, don't love me!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.15,0:37:15.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let me go! Let me go!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.31,0:37:21.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then you shall have a destiny with never leaving my side! Destiny of never leaving my side!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.50,0:37:40.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Leaving these on purpose is also the same. But why purposely tell their whereabouts...?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.42,0:37:42.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there's nothing but to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.17,0:37:45.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}. You haven't seen Renge?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.47,0:37:47.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tamanosuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.64,0:37:50.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These are...! Don't tell me that Rausu...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.77,0:37:54.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were here! We looked for-you, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.39,0:37:55.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is something the matter, you two?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.15,0:37:58.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Renge! Where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.36,0:38:01.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Renge{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.48,0:38:02.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Renge{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.86,0:38:04.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.20,0:38:09.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rausu! Where is Renge? Wait, Rausu!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.00,0:38:16.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let us die together, loved daughter. Together fall to the world of darkness!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.62,0:38:18.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let me go! Let me go!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.29,0:38:20.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, phantom!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.97,0:38:25.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let her go!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.48,0:38:38.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Renge{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.65,0:38:44.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop this immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.07,0:38:45.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sonoko...?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.07,0:38:50.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The phantom of the Konpira theatre... I know that you are not Rausu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.37,0:38:55.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that from the start your intention wasn't a murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.37,0:38:59.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right? Let's finish this already, Romi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.63,0:39:01.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.63,0:39:02.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.13,0:39:06.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right. From the beginning your behaviour was strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.18,0:39:16.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because it was all your own charade!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.44,0:39:20.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was acting? Why would you...?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.56,0:39:23.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, to ensnare Rausu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.20,0:39:33.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Romi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}... Why.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.37,0:39:37.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For revenge. To that man's father.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.33,0:39:40.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The deceased Rausu Companies' predecessor, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.58,0:39:43.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because of that predecessor my father's business was taken...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.59,0:39:48.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An illness that destroyed his body... Mother following him soon after...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.55,0:39:49.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.97,0:39:53.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Being alone, the only thing I could do was to act!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.18,0:39:58.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, I didn't think about a revenge... Then the offer for this play came.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.19,0:40:03.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even now... Even now! I feel like my parents are shouting from the other side!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.94,0:40:05.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So then, my framing...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.36,0:40:08.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But at first, I had no intention to commit a murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.49,0:40:11.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At least, I wanted to destroy this play...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.28,0:40:15.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...and drag the name of the sponsor, the Rausu Companies, to the mud. That would've sufficed!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.12,0:40:18.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then to put pressure on Renge{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.41,0:40:23.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"This child can't do it. She will surely make a huge mistake at the stage", I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.50,0:40:30.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it was a huge success. I had forgotten...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.09,0:40:37.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...that Renge{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} is an actress. Like me, this child should have crumbled under the pressure...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.27,0:40:42.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On top of that, that man found me out.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.48,0:40:51.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With this my loan is cleared, right? Your thoughts?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.57,0:40:56.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right... I couldn't forgive the wrongdoers about my mother and father.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.79,0:41:00.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I should kill this one and make him take the blame! That's what I decided to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.92,0:41:07.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then you called Nabeshima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to the trap, hiding yourself behind the memorial stone and waited.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.92,0:41:13.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the criminal would hit Nabeshima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} from that pedestal... A short person...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.18,0:41:22.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. For example, even a woman it would be possible to hit Nabeshima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} with a deadly blow to his neck.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.15,0:41:28.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That performance tape that was on the cane, is something Rausu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} touched by coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.66,0:41:34.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You thought that the police would think...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.86,0:41:41.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...that Rausu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was trying to steal Renge{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} from Tamanosuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} by framing him, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.83,0:41:47.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then, you showed yourself to Rausu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.42,0:41:52.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By taking back your testimony later, you made the suspicion on Rausu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.97,0:41:58.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Plus, at the park while he was waiting for Tamanosuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you put the projector into his trunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.47,0:42:01.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes...'But as expected, Rausu noticed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.69,0:42:12.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come out! I know the real culprit!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.82,0:42:20.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it's come to this, there is only one way for me, I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.83,0:42:24.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Escaping the police, Rausu and Renge{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} were forced to commit a double suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.79,0:42:30.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But to have that little lady to see through it all...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.64,0:42:42.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't! Romi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.27,0:42:52.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You poor, misfortune man...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.08,0:43:05.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn it! Tamanosuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.33,0:43:07.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.36,0:43:40.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Romi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. To take someone's life... Then even your own! Is that also because of your parents again?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.87,0:43:47.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whatever the circumstances, you've done something that a human should never do!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.58,0:43:52.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't just close your eyes on that. Dying is unforgivable!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.84,0:44:00.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And by leaving such an easy clue, the pamphlet of this place, didn't you want someone to stop you?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.26,0:44:03.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To stop yourself from doing anything else...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.61,0:44:19.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a relief. All thanks to Sonoko.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.03,0:44:22.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did I do it again?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.62,0:44:24.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While you were sleeping, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.62,0:44:30.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry. I will continue with acting. With the chairman, forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.50,0:44:31.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Renge...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.92,0:44:32.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.36,0:46:27.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.78,0:46:30.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This needs some serious kneading.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.54,0:46:32.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But somehow it feels good.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.21,0:46:38.42,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Koshi = Hip; the body of a noodle (Wordplay)
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.21,0:46:38.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My hip is more tired than this udon dough. At least give me some beer, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.63,0:46:43.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He never changes.
